Information about the geographic footprint of the data collection
Acquisition center coordinates. Expected structure is gml:Point/gml:pos.

Acquisition footprint coordinates, described by a closed polygon (last point=first point), using CRS:WGS84, Latitude,Longitude pairs (per-WGS84 definition of point ordering, not necessarily per all WFS implementations). Expected structure is gml:Polygon/gml:exterior/gml:LinearRing/gml:posList.

Determines the orientation of the polygon coordinates for the exterior boundary. Possible values are CW (clockwise) or CCW (counter-clockwise) or OTHER (unspecified). Default value is counter clockwise. Element is only to be provided for products that do not follow the OGC simple features convention.

Extends the EOP Footprint for along track data used in Altimetry products.

A geometry of type GM_Multicurve is used to define the nominal track on the earths surface. This track is essentially a line that is representative of the product but does not include points for every value. The use of GM_MultiCurve allows for multiple lines and breaks in lines. In future wide-swath altimetry cases (e.g. SWOT) where the track will be a swath, the multiExtentOf property in the base schema may be used (as it is for other EO products).
Additional external metadata about the data acquisition.
